        <table class=”a_table”>

        <tr>

        <td>

        <p>

        <br>

        <br>

        <br>

        <b>Amazon.com,inc</b> is an American multinational technology company focusing on e- commerce, cloud computing, online advertising, digital streaming, and artificial intelligence. It has been referred to as “one of the most influential economic and cultural forces in the world”, and is one of the world’s most valuable brands. It is one of the Big Five American information technology companies, alongside Alphabe (Google), Apple, Meta (Facebook), and Microsoft. 

    </p>

<p> Amazon was founded by Jeff Bezos from his garage in Bellevue, Washington, on July 5, 1994 Initially an online marketplace for books, it has expanded into a multitude of product categories, a strategy that has earned it the moniker The Everything Store.

</p>

<p> Amazon, as a company, has several strategic flows that help it to operate and grow its business. Here are some of the key strategic flows of Amazon:

<br>

<div class=”a1”>

<ol>

<li> Customer-centric approach: Amazon’s strategy is centered around the customer. The company strives to provide the best possible customer experience by offering a wide selection of products, fa delivery times, and excellent customer service.

</li>

<br>

<li> Data-driven decision-making: Amazon is known for its data-driven approach to decision-making. The company collects vast amounts of data about customer behavior, sales, and other metrics, and uses this information to make informed decisions about its operations.

</li>

<br><li>Innovation: Amazon is constantly innovating and introducing new products and

Services. The company invests heavily in research and development, and is always looking for new ways to

Improve its operations and offerings.

</li>

<br>

<li> Logistics and supply chain management: Amazon has built a highly efficient logistics and supply chain management system that allows it to deliver products quickly and cost-effectively. The company uses advanced technologies such as machine learning and robotics to streamline its operations and

Improve its delivery times.

</li> <br>

<li> Diversification: Amazon has diversified its business into many different areas, including e-commerce, cloud computing, entertainment, and more. This diversification helps the company to spread its risks and capture opportunities in new markets.

</li> <br>

<li> Platform-based business model: Amazon’s platform-based business model allows it to offer a wide range of products and services through its marketplace. This model allows third-party sellers to se their products on Amazon, which helps to increase the selection and variety of products available to customers

</li> <br>

</ol>

</div> Overall, Amazon’s strategic flows are centered around providing the best possible customer experience, using data to make informed decisions, innovating and diversifying its business, and building an efficient logistics and supply chain management system.

</p> 

</td>

